=============
Form: Create and send data from the form to some places; (http method) get or add data to the database 
  <form action="/where to send the data" method="get/post">
    <input type="email/text/password/..." placeholder="some text">
    <button>LogIn</button>  ===== or <input type="submit">
    <textarea name="" rows="" cols=""></textarea>
  </form>
  
    Form Validation: add 'required' in the input tag.
    ==============  
    Two ways to Label: 
      **use name attribute to give radio button the name petChoice, you can let the user just choose one of the choice. 
      **Use value attribute, you can send the value for each choice, which will reflect in the routes when you submit the form.
    1.
       <lable for="username">UserName:</label> 
       <input name="petChoice" id="username" type="email/text/password/..." placeholder="some text" value="Dog">

    2.
       <lable>UserName: 
          <input name="petChoice" type="email/text/password/..." placeholder="some text" value="Cat">
       </label>
